name: alloc::collections::btree::node::Handle::<collections::btree::node::NodeRef<collections::btree::node::marker::Mut<'a>, K, V, collections::btree::node::marker::Leaf>, collections::btree::node::marker::KV>::split
doc:
Splits the underlying node into three parts:

 - The node is truncated to only contain the key-value pairs to the left of
   this handle.
 - The key and value pointed to by this handle are extracted.
 - All the key-value pairs to the right of this handle are put into a newly
   allocated node.
